          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "D4PI",
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A dedicated 4m arrangement of 12 position-",
                "sensitive parallel-plate avalanche counters was built",
                "in order to measure the photofission fragment angular",
                "and mass distributions simultaneously. Two detectors",
                "provided spatial information as well as the start",
                "signals for the double time-of-flight measurement,",
                "which permitted the fragment mass information to be",
                "deduced. Two hemispheres, each consisting of five",
                "independent detectors, were mounted a distance of",
                "12.5 cm from the target center, and covered a solid",
                "angle of almost 4pi."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The tagging efficiency was measured in",
                "separate calibration runs with a 25.4 cm x 35.6 cm",
                "NaI detector using a very low intensity electron beam",
                "with an endpoint energy of 21 MeV to produce the tagged",
                "photons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A homogeneous 7cm x 10cm fissile target of 400 mu-g/cm2",
                "of 238U evaporated onto a 200mu-g/cm2 mylar foil used.",
                "The target was sandwiched between the two inner",
                "detectors, which are separated by a distance of 1 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
